"content": "<style>\nh1.thlex-title { font-size: 1.3em; margin: 0 0 0.4em; }\n.thlex-key { color: #888; font-size: 0.85em; font-weight: normal; margin-right: 0.4em; }\nnav.thlex-index { margin: 0.5em 0 0.75em; }\nnav.thlex-index ul { margin: 0; padding-left: 1.2em; }\nnav.thlex-index li { margin: 0.15em 0; font-size: 0.95em; }\n.thlex-section { margin: 0.6em 0; }\nh2.thlex-heading { font-size: 1em; margin: 0.5em 0 0.2em; }\nh3.thlex-subheading { font-size: 0.95em; font-weight: normal; font-style: italic; margin: 0.2em 0; }\n.thlex-language-sets { margin: 0.3em 0 0.3em 1em; }\n.thlex-language-set { margin: 0.4em 0; padding-left: 0.75em; border-left: 3px solid #e0e0e0; }\n.thlex-language { font-size: 0.8em; color: #888; margin-right: 0.4em; }\n.thlex-lemma { font-weight: bold; font-family: serif; }\n.thlex-translit { color: #555; font-style: italic; font-size: 0.9em; margin-left: 0.3em; }\n.thlex-refs { font-size: 0.85em; color: #444; margin-top: 0.15em; }\n.thlex-paragraphs p { margin: 0.35em 0; font-size: 0.95em; line-height: 1.5; }\n.thlex-image { margin: 0.5em 0; display: block; }\n.thlex-image img { max-width: 100%; height: auto; display: block; }\nfigcaption.thlex-caption { font-size: 0.85em; color: #555; font-style: italic; margin-top: 0.2em; }\n.thlex-abbr { border-bottom: 1px dotted #888; cursor: help; }\n.thlex-xref { color: #1a5fb4; }\nspan[data-bnType=\"bibleReference\"] { color: #1a5fb4; }\ntable.thlex-table { border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 0.9em; margin: 0.5em 0; }\ntable.thlex-table td { padding: 0.2em 0.6em; vertical-align: top; border: 1px solid #ddd; }\ntable.thlex-table tr:first-child td { font-weight: bold; background: #f5f5f5; }\nul.thlex-index-list { margin: 0.4em 0; padding-left: 1.4em; font-size: 0.95em; line-height: 1.6; }\nul.thlex-index-list ul { margin: 0.1em 0; padding-left: 1.4em; }\n.thlex-index-key { font-weight: bold; font-style: italic; }\n</style><h1 class=\"thlex-title\" id=\"REALIA:1.5.2.1\"><span class=\"thlex-key\">1.5.2.1</span> Engraving, carving</h1><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">References:</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-sets\">\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">חרשׁ, חָרָשׁ</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(charash)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod28:11\">EXO 28:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod35:35\">EXO 35:35</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod38:23\">EXO 38:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer17:1\">JER 17:1</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">חֲרֹשֶׁת</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(charosheth)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod31:5\">EXO 31:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod31:5\">EXO 31:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod35:33\">EXO 35:33</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod35:33\">EXO 35:33</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">פתח</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(pathach (verb))</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod28:9\">EXO 28:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod28:11\">EXO 28:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod28:36\">EXO 28:36</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod39:6\">EXO 39:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs7:36\">1KI 7:36</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr2:6\">2CH 2:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr2:13\">2CH 2:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr3:7\">2CH 3:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech3:9\">ZEC 3:9</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">פִּתּוּחַ</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(pituach)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod28:11\">EXO 28:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod28:21\">EXO 28:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod28:36\">EXO 28:36</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod39:6\">EXO 39:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod39:14\">EXO 39:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod39:30\">EXO 39:30</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr2:6\">2CH 2:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr2:13\">2CH 2:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps74:6\">PSA 74:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech3:9\">ZEC 3:9</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">קלע, מִקְלַעַת</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(qala‘ (verb), miqla‘ath)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs6:18\">1KI 6:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs6:29\">1KI 6:29</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs6:29\">1KI 6:29</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs6:32\">1KI 6:32</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs6:32\">1KI 6:32</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs6:35\">1KI 6:35</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs7:31\">1KI 7:31</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Greek</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">γλύμμα</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(glumma)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Sir38:27\">SIR 38:27</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Sir45:11\">SIR 45:11</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Greek</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">γλυφή</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(glufē)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Wis18:24\">WIS 18:24</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Greek</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">γλύφω</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(glufō (verb))</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Wis13:13\">WIS 13:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Sir38:27\">SIR 38:27</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Greek</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">ἐγγλύφω</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(egglufō (verb))</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Macc13:29\">1MA 13:29</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Greek</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">κολάπτω</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(kolaptō (verb))</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Sir45:11\">SIR 45:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/3Macc2:27\">3MA 2:27</a></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">Description:</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-paragraphs\">\n<p>\n            <figure class=\"thlex-image\"><img class=\"thlex-img\" src=\"images/WEB-0341_engraving_ring.jpg\" alt=\"Engraving on a ring\"><figcaption class=\"thlex-caption\">Engraving on a ring (© The Portable Antiquities Scheme/ The Trustees of the British Museum, CC BY-SA 2.0, via Wikimedia Commons)</figcaption></figure>An engraving was a picture or words made by scratching lines in a hard surface such as stone, metal, or gems. A carving was a figure usually made out of wood, using a knife or another sharp implement.</p>\n<hr/>\n</div>\n</div><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">Translation:</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-paragraphs\">\n<p>In some languages it may be necessary to choose a verb for “engrave” according to the surface that is being used.</p>\n<p>The Hebrew word <em>charosheth</em> is used in <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod31:5\">EXO 31:5</a> and <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod35:33\">EXO 35:33</a> to describe both engraving and carving.</p>\n<p>The specific action described in <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Sir38:27\">SIR 38:27</a> is “engrave seals” (<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"New Jerusalem Bible (1985)\">NJB</abbr>; compare the even more precise <abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Revised Standard Version (1952)\">RSV</abbr> rendering “cut the signets of seals”; see also the discussion at <a class=\"thlex-xref\" data-bnType=\"lexiconLink\" data-collection=\"\" data-key=\"\" href=\"#\">10.2 Seal, signet ring, ring&lt;REALIA:10.2&gt;</a>). The point of the passage is the diligence and precision with which the engraver works. Where there is no exact equivalent of signets or seals, it is possible to refer to some other craftsman’s work that requires precision and can be done in great variety.</p>\n</div>\n</div>",
